{{distinguish|Lada Niva}} {{Infobox automobile | name = Chevrolet Niva | image = File:Шевроле-Нива 2015 год.JPG | manufacturer = [[GM-AvtoVAZ]] | aka = | production = 1998–present | assembly = [[Tolyatti]], [[Samara Oblast]], [[Russia]] | predecessor = | successor = | class = [[Mini SUV]] | body_style = 5-door [[Station wagon|wagon]] | layout = [[Front-engine, four-wheel-drive layout|Front-engine, four-wheel-drive]] | engine = 1.7 L [[Inline-four engine|I4]] ([[Petrol engine|petrol]]) | transmission = 5-speed [[Manual transmission|manual]] | wheelbase = {{convert|2450|mm|in|1|abbr=on}}<ref>{{cite web|title=Размеры Chevrolet Niva|language=Russian|url=http://www.chevrolet.ru/avtomobili/crossovers_suvs/niva/features-and-specs/dimension.html|publisher=Chevrolet Россия|accessdate=3 January 2014|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140104140505/http://www.chevrolet.ru/avtomobili/crossovers_suvs/niva/features-and-specs/dimension.html|archivedate=4 January 2014}}</ref> | length = {{convert|4056|mm|in|1|abbr=on}} | width = {{convert|1800|mm|in|1|abbr=on}} | height = {{convert|1690|mm|in|1|abbr=on}} | related = [[Lada Niva]] }}
The '''Chevrolet Niva''' is a mini [[sport utility vehicle]] (SUV) produced by [[GM-AvtoVAZ]], a joint venture between [[AvtoVAZ]] (the parent company of the [[Lada]] brand) and [[General Motors]], since 1998. The car is a development of the [[Lada Niva]] and was previously known as the VAZ-2123 in the design stage.
==First generation== [[File:Нива Ваз 2123 1.JPG|thumb|left|VAZ-2123 (1998–2002)]] [[File:Chevrolet Niva Silver.jpg|thumb|left|Chevrolet Niva (2003–2009)]] It features an updated body and 1.7-litre gasoline engine with [[fuel injection]]. Although the body and the interiors are new, it is still based on the old VAZ 2121 engine, transmission and most mechanicals.
In 2003 the car was awarded zero stars out of a possible four by the Russian [[ARCAP]] safety assessment program.<ref>{{cite web|title=Chevrolet Niva|url=https://autoreview.ru/arcap/cars/Chevrolet/Niva|website=Авторевю|accessdate=1 June 2017}}</ref>
An export version with reinforced hull, 1.8-litre Opel [[GM Family 1 engine#Ecotec|Ecotec Family 1]] gasoline engine and [[Aisin]] [[four-wheel drive]] has been under consideration since 2003. Although most of the engineering work has been completed, the release has been constantly postponed. Although the GM-AvtoVAZ considered building a new engine plant for the local production of Ecotecs, in July 2005 it was announced that the project was cancelled, along with plans for the long-anticipated "export" Niva. However, the project was revived in Fall 2006 and the "Niva FAM1" was introduced as a new trim level for the 2007 model year. The price was much higher than the standard trim, that made the project not as successful and led it to be discontinued in April 2008. Another reason was the ceasing of Ecotec engine production at the Hungarian plant.<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://www.autonavigator.ru/news/2008/04/25/9529.html |title=Chevrolet Niva FAM1 больше не выпускается |language=Russian |publisher=AutoNavigator.ru |date= |accessdate=27 March 2010}}</ref>
In 2009, the model got a minor update, featuring a slight restyling, done by [[Gruppo Bertone|Bertone]] studio and some minor-changes.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://gm-avtovaz.ru/chevrolet_niva/about/ |title=О Chevrolet NIVA |language=Russian |publisher=Gm-AvtoVAZ.ru |date= |accessdate=1 February 2011}}</ref> The GLS and GLC version also comes with improved safety, such as ABS and dual front airbags.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.niva-chevrolet.com.ua/chevrolet-niva-new.html |script-title=ru:Нива Шевроле |publisher=Niva-Chevrolet.com.ua |language=Russian |accessdate=3 November 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131104214552/http://www.niva-chevrolet.com.ua/chevrolet-niva-new.html/ |archivedate=4 November 2013 }}</ref>
{{clear}}
==Second generation concept== {{Infobox automobile | name = Chevrolet Niva Concept | image = Chevrolet Niva Concept.JPG | caption = Chevrolet Niva Concept | manufacturer = [[GM-AvtoVAZ]] | aka = | production = | model_years = | assembly = [[Tolyatti]], [[Samara Oblast]], [[Russia]] | designer = Ondrej Koromház | class = [[Mini SUV]] | body_style = 5-door [[Station wagon|wagon]] | layout = [[Front-engine, four-wheel-drive layout|Front-engine, four-wheel-drive]] | platform = | related = | engine = 1.8 L [[Inline-four engine|I4]] ([[Petrol engine|petrol]]) | transmission = 5-speed [[Manual transmission|manual]] | wheelbase = | length = | width = | height = | weight = | predecessor = | successor = | sp = us }}
GM-AvtoVAZ introduced a concept vehicle for a new generation of the Chevrolet Niva at the [[Moscow International Automobile Salon]] in late August 2014.<ref name="concept">{{cite web|title=Концепт Chevrolet NIVA нового поколения на ММАС 2014|url=http://media.gm.com/media/ru/ru/chevrolet/news.detail.html/content/Pages/news/ru/ru/2014/chevrolet/08-13-niva-concept.html|publisher=Chevrolet Media|accessdate=24 August 2014|language=Russian|date=13 August 2014}}</ref> The Niva Concept, designed by Ondrej Koromház of GM (or at General Motors' headquarters in Melbourne according to other sources),<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.caradvice.com.au/516693/new-lada-niva-for-2018-could-it-be/|title=New Lada Niva for 2018… Could it be?|publisher=Caradvice.com.au}}</ref> had a longitudinal mounted engine, full-time four-wheel-drive, two-gear transfer case and rigid-axle rear suspension. The production model was supposed to get a 1.8-liter [[PSA Peugeot Citroën]] EC8 engine (135&nbsp;hp) paired with a 5-speed manual gearbox,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://wroom.ru/en/news/2572 |title=Chevrolet Niva Concept debuted in Moscow |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=28 August 2014 |website=Wroom.ru |accessdate=2 September 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141209110538/http://wroom.ru/en/news/2572 |archivedate=9 December 2014 }}</ref> although more recent news reports suggested that it was planned to be based on the [[Renault Duster]] platform.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.news-original.ru/gm-avtovaz-is-preparing-a-chevrolet-niva-2-on-the-platform-of-renault-duster.html|title=«GM-AVTOVAZ» is preparing a Chevrolet Niva 2 on the platform of Renault Duster|publisher=News-original.ru|access-date=2017-03-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170308222614/http://en.news-original.ru/gm-avtovaz-is-preparing-a-chevrolet-niva-2-on-the-platform-of-renault-duster.html|archive-date=2017-03-08|url-status=dead}}</ref> The new model's production version was initially expected in 2016,<ref name="concept"/> but following Chevrolet stopping sales of its mainstream models in Russia, no information has been released on the topic. In September of 2018, it was reported that GM has suspended all the work on planned replacement of Chevrolet Niva.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.autonews.com/article/20180921/COPY01/309219979/gm-suspends-work-on-chevrolet-niva-replacement|title=GM suspends work on Chevrolet Niva replacement|publisher=[[Automotive News]]}}</ref>
