* 2012 Car of the Year in [[Denmark]]. In October 2011, 18 Danish motor journalists chose the Opel Ampera as "Car of the Year 2012" by a wide margin, despite being more expensive than the family cars the award usually goes to.<ref>{{cite news|author=Steen Bachmann|url=http://bilmagasinet.dk/article/78864-uventet-karing-opel-ampera-er-arets-bil-i-danmark-2012|title=Uventet kåring: Opel Ampera er Årets Bil i Danmark 2012|work=Bil Magasinet|date=2011-10-12|accessdate=2011-10-14|language=Danish}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|author=Sebastian Krausing|url=http://www.bilsektionen.dk/arets-bil-i-danmark-2012-er-opel-ampera/|title=Årets bil i Danmark 2012 - Opel Ampera|work=Bilsektionen.dk|date=2011-10-12|accessdate=2011-10-14|language=Danish}}</ref>
* 2012 [[European Car of the Year]], shared by the Chevrolet Volt and the Opel/Vauxhall.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hybridcars.com/news/volt-and-ampera-win-european-car-year-42204.html|title=Volt and Ampera Win European Car Of The Year|author=Huw Evans|work=HybridCars.com|date=2012-03-06|accessdate=2012-03-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120308192839/http://www.hybridcars.com/news/volt-and-ampera-win-european-car-year-42204.html|archive-date=2012-03-08|url-status = dead}}</ref> The Ampera/Volt became the first car developed in the U.S. to win this European award.<ref name=DTN042012>{{cite news|url=http://www.detroitnews.com/article/20120417/AUTO0103/204170360/1121/auto01/GM%C3%ADs-Opel-Ampera-surpasses-sales-goals|title=GM's Opel Ampera surpasses sales goals|author=Melissa Burden|work=[[The Detroit News]]|date=2012-04-10|accessdate=2012-04-17}}{{dead link|date=September 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Squatriglia |first=Chuck |url=https://www.wired.com/autopia/2012/03/volt-ampera-europe-car-year/ |title=Chevrolet Volt Named European Car of the Year &#124; Autopia |website=Wired.com |date=2012-03-05 |accessdate=2013-11-29}}</ref>
* 2013 Green Mobility Trophy. Readers of [[Auto Zeitung]] in Germany awarded the Opel Ampera the trophy and named the mid-size sedan the best electric vehicle.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://insideevs.com/opel-ampera-beat-tesla-model-s-and-bmw-i3-to-win-green-mobility-trophy-2013/|title=Opel Ampera Beat Tesla Model S and BMW i3 to Win "Green Mobility Trophy 2013″|author=Eric Loveday|work=InsideEVs.com|date=2013-08-27|accessdate=2013-09-01}}</ref>

;Rest of the world organizations

* 2012 Drive's Green Innovation Award to the Holden Volt, as part of the Australia's Drive Car of the Year Awards.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.international.to/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=7375:holden-volt-wins-drives-green-innovation-award&catid=64:business&Itemid=286|title=Holden Volt wins Drive's Green Innovation Award|work=The International News Magazine|date=2012-12-07|accessdate=2012-12-23|url-status = dead|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20130419010329/http://www.international.to/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=7375:holden-volt-wins-drives-green-innovation-award&catid=64:business&Itemid=286|archivedate=2013-04-19|df=}}</ref>

