{{About|the Chevrolet Series F of 1917|the Chevrolet Superior Series F of 1924|Chevrolet Superior}} {{Infobox automobile | image= | caption = | assembly = | weight = | wheelbase = {{convert|108|in|mm|0|abbr=on}} | designer = | name = Chevrolet Series F | aka = {{ubl|F-2 Chevrolet Royal Mail Roadster|F-5 Chevrolet Baby Grand Touring}} | manufacturer = [[Chevrolet]] | production = 1917 | predecessor = [[Chevrolet Series H]] | successor = [[Chevrolet Series FA]] | class = [[mid-size]] | body_style = {{ubl|F-2 2-door roadster|F-5 4-door touring}} | engine = {{convert|171|in3|L|abbr=on}}, {{convert|24|hp|abbr=on}}, [[straight-4|I4]] | transmission = | layout = [[FR layout]] | related = }}
The '''Chevrolet Series F''' of 1917 was an American automobile manufactured by [[Chevrolet]]. The successor of the [[Chevrolet Series H|Series H]], it had a longer wheelbase and other improvements, but kept the same engine. It was replaced the following year by the [[Chevrolet Series FA|Series FA]] in 1918, which had a larger, more powerful engine.
==Technical features== The F had a [[wheelbase]] of 108&nbsp;inches. It had the same four-cylinder engine as the H, with a displacement of 171&nbsp;cubic inches and 24 horsepower.
==Engine specifications== *Overhead-valve *Inline *Four-cylinder cast-iron block *Bore and stroke: 3 11/16 × 4 in *Displacement: 171 cid *Brake hp: 24 HP *Main bearings: three *Valve lifters: solid *Carburetor: Zenith double jet <ref>{{cite book | last = Gunnell | first = John | title = Standard Catalog of Chevrolet, 1912–2003: 90&nbsp;Years of History, Photos, Technical Data and Pricing | publisher = [[Krause Publications]] |page=13 |isbn=978-1-4402-3051-6}}</ref>
==Models==
The Series F preserved the model names and body styles of the Series H it replaced: the '''Royal Mail''' model F-2 roadster and the '''Baby Grand''' model F-5 open touring car.
On both models, the front fenders followed a straight line from right behind the center of the front wheels to the runningboard.<ref>{{cite book | last = Gunnell | first = John | title = Standard Catalog of Chevrolet, 1912–2003: 90&nbsp;Years of History, Photos, Technical Data and Pricing | publisher = [[Krause Publications]] |isbn=978-1-4402-3051-6}}</ref>
