The '''Chevrolet Tracker''' (创酷) in China is a subcompact [[Crossover (vehicle)|crossover SUV]] produced by [[SAIC-GM]] for the Chinese market.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.autonews.com/shanghai-auto-show/chevy-revives-trailblazer-tracker-china|title=Chevy revives Trailblazer, Tracker for China}}</ref>

==Overview==
[[File:2019 Chevrolet Tracker 003.jpg|thumb|left|2019 Chevrolet Tracker rear]]
The Chevrolet Tracker in the Chinese market was revealed in 2019 alongside the Trailblazer. The Chinese market Tracker was designed to replace the Chevrolet Trax in China, and shares the same Chinese name as the Chevrolet Trax. On the side note, the Chevrolet Trax was also called the Tracker in several other markets.

Despite the use of the Tracker name, the Chinese market Tracker is not related to the [[Chevrolet Tracker (Americas)|Chevrolet Tracker]] sold in North America as a rebadged Suzuki Escudo from the 1990s to the 2000s.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.motor1.com/news/344929/chevrolet-trailblazer-tracker-shanghai-debut/|title=Chevrolet Trailblazer And Tracker Debut Modern Looks In China}}</ref>

The GEM platform which the Chinese market Tracker was built on was designed for developing automotive markets including China, Latin America and Southeast Asia. The Chevrolet Tracker launched in China in 2019 is one of the vehicles with the GEM platform and is therefore not intended for the US and Canada.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://gmauthority.com/blog/2019/04/all-new-chevrolet-tracker-introduced-in-china/|title=All-New Chevrolet Tracker Introduced In China}}</ref>

==Engines==
The Chinese market Tracker is available with a 3-cylinder 1.0 turbo engine producing 84&nbsp;kW and a 3-cylinder 1.3 turbo engine producing 121&nbsp;kW.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://chejiahao.autohome.com.cn/info/3608349#pvareaid=28086821198|title=雪佛兰创界Trailblazer及创酷Tracker亮相上海车展}}</ref>
{{clear}}

