{{Infobox electric vehicle | name = Chevrolet Menlo | image = | caption = | manufacturer = [[Chevrolet]] ([[SAIC-GM]]) | aka = Chevrolet Menlo EV | production = 2020–present | model_years = 2020–present | assembly = | class = [[Compact car]] ([[C-segment|C]]) | body_style = 5-door [[liftback]] | layout = [[Front-engine, front-wheel-drive layout|Front-engine, front-wheel drive]] | platform = | engine = | motor = 1x {{convert|110|kW|hp|abbr=on}} permanent magnet motor/generators | transmission = Fixed gear ratio | drivetrain = | battery = 52.5 [[kWh]] [[lithium-ion battery|lithium-ion]] | range = | electric_range = {{Convert|410|km|abbr=on}} | charging = {{unbulleted list | [[Alternating current|AC]]: 8 hours | [[Direct current|DC]] Fast Charge: 0.67 hours to 80%}} | wheelbase = {{Convert|2660|mm|abbr=on}} | length = {{Convert|4665|mm|abbr=on}} | width = {{Convert|1813|mm|abbr=on}} | height = {{Convert|1538|mm|abbr=on}} | weight = {{Convert|1660|kg|abbr=on}} | related = [[Buick Velite 6]] | designer = | predecessor = | sp = }}
The '''Chevrolet Menlo''' (畅巡) is an [[electric vehicle|electric]] compact wagon/CUV, sold exclusively in China. It is the first Chevrolet EV available in China, as the [[Chevrolet Bolt]] is not sold there.<ref name="gma20200220" />
==History==
The Chevrolet Menlo is based on the Chevrolet FNR-X concept shown at the 2017 [[Auto Shanghai]] show. The production version of the Menlo debuted at a gala event in [[Hefei]], Anhui on November 8, 2019<ref>{{cite press release| url=https://media.gm.com/media/cn/en/chevrolet/home.detail.html/content/Pages/news/cn/en/2019/Nov/1108_Chevrolet_Menlo_EV_and_Blazer_SUV.html| title=Chevrolet Menlo EV and Chevrolet Blazer SUV Make China Debut| publisher=General Motors| date=8 November 2019}}</ref>, and was also shown at the 2019 [[Auto Guangzhou]] show. Pre-ordering began in December, and deliveries started on February 20, 2020.<ref name="gma20200220">{{cite web| url=https://gmauthority.com/blog/2020/02/all-new-chevrolet-menlo-ev-officially-launches-in-china/| title=All-New Chevrolet Menlo EV Officially Launches In China| first=Deivis | last=Centeno| publisher=GM Authority| date=20 February 2020}}</ref>
Thanks to a government subsidy of up to 100,000 yuan (approximately $14,250 USD), the Menlo is the lowest-priced compact electric crossover in China.<ref name="gma20200220" />
Unlike the rest of the Chevrolet's models, the Menlo has a unique trim level naming scheme, which includes Starshare, Galaxy, Nebula and Starlux. It also features three driving modes (standard, sport, and economy) and three levels of energy recycling.<ref name="gma20200220" />
==Battery==
The Menlo has a lithium-ion battery, with 52.5 kWh capacity and a range of up to 410 km on the [[New European Driving Cycle|NEDC]]. It generates up to {{convert|110|kW|hp PS|0|abbr=on}} and {{convert|350|Nm|lbft|0|abbr=on}} torque.<ref name="gma20200220" /> This battery is also used in the [[Buick Velite 6]] Plus.
